# Command lfk

## What does this command do:

Lightning-fast, keyboard-focused, yazi-inspired terminal user interface for navigating and managing Kubernetes clusters.

## Installed from

For Fedora install using: curl -sSfL https://github.com/janosmiko/lfk/releases/download/v0.9.24/lfk_0.9.24_linux_amd64.tar.gz | tar -xz -C ~/.local/bin lfk && chmod +x ~/.local/bin/lfk
For Raspberry Pi install using: curl -sSfL https://github.com/janosmiko/lfk/releases/download/v0.9.24/lfk_0.9.24_linux_arm64.tar.gz | tar -xz -C ~/.local/bin lfk && chmod +x ~/.local/bin/lfk
For Mac install using: brew install janosmiko/tap/lfk

## Command path

For Fedora run: ~/.local/bin/lfk
For Raspberry Pi run: ~/.local/bin/lfk
For Mac run: /opt/homebrew/bin/lfk

## Command documentation

Docs can be found at https://github.com/janosmiko/lfk

## Command options

# Use default kubeconfig (~/.kube/config + ~/.kube/config.d/*)
lfk

# Start in a specific context
lfk --context my-cluster

# Start in a specific namespace (disables all-namespaces mode)
lfk -n kube-system

# Start with multiple namespaces
lfk -n default -n kube-system

# Use a specific config file
lfk --config /path/to/config.yaml

# Use a specific kubeconfig
lfk --kubeconfig /path/to/kubeconfig

# Disable mouse capture (enables native terminal text selection)
lfk --no-mouse

# Disable all colors
lfk --no-color

# Override watch-mode polling interval (default 2s)
lfk --watch-interval 5s

# Key bindings (in-app)
# h/l or Left/Right  Navigate parent/child level
# j/k or Down/Up     Move cursor
# x                  Action menu (logs, exec, delete, scale, port-forward, etc.)
# L                  View logs
# v                  Describe resource
# D / X              Delete / force delete
# y / Y              Copy name / YAML to clipboard
# f                  Filter items
# /                  Search
# \                  Namespace selector
# A                  Toggle all-namespaces
# T                  Open theme selector
# ?                  Toggle help screen
# :                  Command bar (resource jumps, kubectl, shell commands)
# w                  Toggle watch mode
# Ctrl+S             Toggle secret value visibility
# Space              Toggle multi-selection
